#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:20(para)
msgid ""
"This section describes how to keep your computer safe from security threats."
msgstr ""
"Cette section décrit comment maintenir la sécurité de votre ordinateur vis à "
"vis des menaces inhérentes."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:22(title)
msgid "Using separate users"
msgstr "Utilisation de comptes utilisateurs distincts"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:23(para)
msgid ""
"During installation of Ubuntu, a single user and password is created. "
"However, in order to keep your computer and documents safe, it is important "
"to use a separate user account for each person that uses the computer. In "
"this way, multiple users can have access to the computer while preserving "
"and protecting their own personal settings and files."
msgstr ""
"Pendant l'installation d'Ubuntu, un seul utilisateur et mot de passe est "
"créé. Cependant, afin de maintenir votre ordinateur et vos documents en "
"sécurité, il est important d'avoir un compte d'utilisateur distinct pour "
"chaque personne qui se sert de l'ordinateur. De cette façon, plusieurs "
"utilisateurs peuvent avoir accès à l'ordinateur tout en préservant et en "
"protégeant leurs paramètres et fichiers personnels."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:24(para)
msgid ""
"On Ubuntu, each user has their own <emphasis>home directory</emphasis> in "
"which files and settings are stored. Furthermore, each user can be part of "
"one or more <emphasis>groups</emphasis>, which define which parts of the "
"system that user has access to."
msgstr ""
"Sur Ubuntu, chaque utilisateur dispose de son propre <emphasis>répertoire "
"personnel</emphasis> dans lequel sont stockés ses fichiers et paramètres. De "
"plus, chaque utilisateur peut faire partie d'un ou plusieurs "
"<emphasis>groupes</emphasis>, qui définissent quelles parties du système lui "
"sont accessibles."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:27(para)
msgid ""
"You may need administrative rights to make some of the changes detailed "
"below. See <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"ghelp:administrative\">Administrative "
"tasks</ulink> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez avoir besoin des droits administratifs pour effectuer certains "
"des changements détaillés ci-dessous. Consultez <ulink type=\"help\" "
"url=\"ghelp:administrative\">Tâches administratives</ulink> pour plus "
"d'information."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:31(title)
msgid "Managing users"
msgstr "Gestion des utilisateurs"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:32(para)
msgid ""
"To modify the users or groups on your system, you can use the "
"<application>Users And Groups</application> application located in "
"<menuchoice"
"><guimenu>System</guimenu><guimenuitem>Administration</guimenuitem>"
"<guimenuitem>Users and Groups</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Pour modifier les utilisateurs ou les groupes sur votre système, vous pouvez "
"utiliser l'application <application>Utilisateurs et groupes</application> "
"située dans "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Système</guimenu><guimenuitem>Administration<"
"/guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Utilisateurs et groupes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:33(para)
msgid ""
"To add a new user, click on <guilabel>Add user</guilabel>, enter the "
"required information and then click <guilabel>OK</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Pour ajouter un nouvel utilisateur, cliquez sur <guilabel>Ajouter un "
"utilisateur</guilabel>, renseignez les informations requises et cliquez sur "
"<guilabel>OK</guilabel>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:34(para)
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"To edit the properties of each user, click the "
"<guilabel>Properties</guilabel> button located in the main "
"<guilabel>Users</guilabel> window."
msgstr ""
"Pour modifier les propriétés de chaque utilisateur, cliquez sur le bouton "
"<guilabel>Propriétés</guilabel> qui se trouve dans la fenêtre "
"<guilabel>Utilisateurs</guilabel> principale."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:35(para)
msgid ""
"To give a new user administrative rights (see <ulink type=\"help\" "
"url=\"ghelp:administrative\">Administrative Tasks</ulink>), edit that user's "
"properties and, under the <guilabel>User Privileges</guilabel> tab, ensure "
"that the <guilabel>Administer the system</guilabel> box is checked."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:39(title)
msgid "Managing groups of users"
msgstr "Gérer les groupes d'utilisateurs"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:40(para)
msgid ""
"To add a new group, select the <guilabel>Groups</guilabel> tab and click "
"<guilabel>Add group</guilabel>. Choose a name for the new group and, if you "
"want, change the default value for the <guilabel>Group ID</guilabel>. If you "
"try to allocate a <guilabel>Group ID</guilabel> that is in use, the system "
"will warn you."
msgstr ""
"Pour ajouter un nouveau groupe, sélectionnez l'onglet "
"<guilabel>Groupes</guilabel> et cliquez sur <guilabel>Ajouter un groupe "
"…</guilabel>. Choisissez un nom pour le nouveau groupe et, si vous le "
"souhaitez, changez la valeur par défaut de l'<guilabel>ID Groupe</guilabel>. "
"Si vous tentez d'attribuer un <guilabel>ID Groupe</guilabel> déjà utilisé, "
"le système vous en informera."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:41(para)
msgid ""
"You can add users to the newly created group by selecting a user from the "
"left menu and clicking on the <guilabel>Add</guilabel> button. Removing a "
"user is as simple as adding one: select a user from the right menu then "
"click <guilabel>Remove</guilabel>. When you are ready, click "
"<guilabel>OK</guilabel> and the new group with its users, if inserted, will "
"be created."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez ajouter des utilisateurs au groupe nouvellement créé en en "
"sélectionnant un depuis le menu de gauche puis en cliquant sur le bouton "
"<guilabel>Ajouter</guilabel>. Enlever un utilisateur d'un groupe est aussi "
"simple que d'en ajouter un : sélectionnez-en un dans le menu de droite et "
"cliquez sur <guilabel>Enlever</guilabel>. Lorsque vous avez fini, cliquez "
"sur <guilabel>OK</guilabel>, et le nouveau groupe, avec, le cas échéant, ses "
"utilisateurs, sera créé."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:42(para)
msgid ""
"To edit the properties of a group, from within the "
"<guilabel>Groups</guilabel> main window choose a group name and click on the "
"<guilabel>Properties</guilabel> button."
msgstr ""
"Pour modifier les propriétés d'un groupe, séléctionnez un nom de groupe "
"depuis la fenêtre principale <guilabel>Groupes</guilabel> et cliquez sur le "
"bouton <guilabel>Propriétés</guilabel>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:43(para)
msgid ""
"To remove a user or a group from the system, select the user or group you "
"want to delete and click <guilabel>Delete</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Pour enlever un utilisateur ou un groupe du système, sélectionnez "
"l'utilisateur ou le groupe que vous désirez supprimer et cliquez sur "
"<guilabel>Supprimer</guilabel>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:49(title)
msgid "Update your computer"
msgstr "Mettre à jour votre ordinateur"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:50(para)
msgid ""
"Sometimes the Ubuntu developers release feature and security updates for "
"applications and packages within the Ubuntu system. You should update your "
"computer in order to keep it safe."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:52(para)
msgid ""
"When updates are available, Ubuntu will inform you with a message and an "
"icon in your notification area. To update your system:"
msgstr ""
"Quand des mises à jour sont disponibles, Ubuntu vous informera avec un "
"message et un icône dans la zone de notification. Pour mettre à jour votre "
"système :"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:54(para)
msgid ""
"Click the icon in the notification area, enter your password and press "
"<guibutton>OK</guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez l'icône dans la zone de notification, saisissez votre mot de passe "
"et cliquez sur <guibutton>OK</guibutton>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:56(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>Update Manager</application> program will list the "
"available updates. To install these updates, press <guibutton>Install "
"Updates</guibutton>. Ubuntu will then download and install the available "
"updates from the Internet."
msgstr ""
"Le <application>Gestionnaire de mises à jour</application> affichera une "
"liste des mises à jour disponibles. Pour les installer, cliquez sur le "
"<guibutton>Installer les mises à jour</guibutton>. Ubuntu téléchargera alors "
"les mises à jour disponibles depuis Internet et les installera."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:58(para)
msgid ""
"When <application>Update Manager</application> has finished updating your "
"system, close the pop-up window with the <guibutton>Close</guibutton> "
"button, then close <application>Update Manager</application> to finish "
"updating your system."
msgstr ""
"Une fois que le <application>Gestionnaire de mises à jour</application> a "
"terminé la mise à jour du système, fermez la boîte de dialogue avec le "
"bouton <guibutton>Fermer</guibutton>, puis fermez le "
"<application>Gestionnaire de mises à jour</application>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:61(para)
msgid ""
"After installing some important updates, it may be necessary to restart your "
"computer. If so, Ubuntu will inform you with a message and an icon in your "
"notification area."
msgstr ""
"Après l'installation de mises à jour importantes, il peut être nécessaire de "
"redémarrer votre ordinateur. Si c'est le cas, Ubuntu affichera un message et "
"un icône dans la zone de notification pour vous en informer."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:62(para)
msgid ""
"To manually check for updates, press "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu><gui"
"menuitem>Administration</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Update "
"Manager</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Pour vérifier manuellement si des mises à jour sont disponibles, allez dans "
"<m"
"enuchoice><guimenu>Système</guimenu><guimenuitem>Administration</guimenuitem"
"><guimenuitem>Gestionnaire de mises à jour</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:63(para)
msgid ""
"To change software update settings, press "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu"
"><guimenuitem>Administration</guimenuitem><guimenuitem>Software "
"Sources</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, enter your password and then click the "
"<guilabel>Internet Updates</guilabel> tab."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:67(title)
msgid "Lock your screen while away"
msgstr "Verrouiller votre écran lorsque vous êtes absent"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:68(para)
msgid ""
"Locking your screen prevents other people from accessing your computer while "
"you are away from it. All of your applications and work remain open while "
"the screen is locked, and the screensaver is displayed."
msgstr ""
"Vérrouiller votre écran empêche d'autres personnes d'accéder à votre "
"ordinateur lorsque vous en êtes absent. Toutes vos applications et votre "
"travail resteront ouverts pendant que l'écran est verrouillé, et "
"l'économiseur d'écran sera affiché."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:69(para)
msgid "You can lock your screen in one of the following ways:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez vérrouiller votre écran par l'une des méthodes suivantes :"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:72(para)
msgid ""
"Press "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu><guimenuitem>Quit...</guimenuitem><"
"guimenuitem>Lock Screen</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Choissisez "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Système</guimenu><guimenuitem>Quitter...</guim"
"enuitem><guimenuitem>Vérrouiller l'écranguimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:75(para)
msgid ""
"Press "
"<keycombo><keycap>Control</keycap><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>L</keycap>"
"</keycombo> to lock the screen. This keyboard shortcut can be changed in "
"<menu"
"choice><guimenu>System</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem><gu"
"imenuitem>Keyboard Shortcuts</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:78(para)
msgid ""
"You can add a <guibutton>Lock Screen</guibutton> button to a panel for easy "
"access. Right-click a panel (for example, the panel at the top of the "
"screen), select <guibutton>Add to Panel...</guibutton> and drag the "
"<guibutton>Lock Screen</guibutton> item to the desired location."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:79(para)
msgid ""
"To unlock the screen, move the mouse or press a key. Then, type your "
"password and either press the <keycap>Return</keycap> key or press the "
"<guibutton>Unlock</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:80(para)
msgid ""
"If more than one person has a user account on your computer and the screen "
"is locked, other users can press the <guibutton>Switch user...</guibutton> "
"button to use the computer, even while the screen is locked. They will be "
"unable to access your currently-open work, and you will be able to switch "
"back to your locked session when they have finished using the computer."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:83(title)
msgid "Set up a firewall"
msgstr "Paramétrer un pare-feu"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:84(para)
msgid ""
"You can optionally install a firewall to protect your computer against "
"unauthorized access by people on the Internet or your network. Firewalls "
"block connections to your computer from unknown sources, which helps to "
"prevent security breaches."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:87(para)
msgid ""
"Install the <application>firestarter</application> package from the "
"<quote>Universe</quote> repository (see <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"ghelp:add-"
"applications\">Add Applications</ulink>)."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:90(para)
msgid ""
"To start <application>Firestarter</application>, choose "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>S"
"ystem</guimenu><guisubmenu>Administration</guisubmenu><g"
"uimenuitem>Firestarter</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, and enter your "
"administrator password when prompted."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:94(para)
msgid ""
"The <application>Firewall Wizard</application> should run. If it does not, "
"press <menuchoice><guimenu>Firewall</guimenu><guimenuitem>Run "
"Wizard</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:97(para)
msgid ""
"Follow the steps in the <application>Firewall Wizard</application>. After "
"completing all of the steps, the firewall should be configured and running."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:100(para)
msgid ""
"To check that your firewall is working correctly, make use of an online "
"firewall testing service such as <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.grc.com/\">ShieldsUP</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:103(para)
msgid ""
"For help and advice on the advanced configuration of "
"<application>Firestarter</application>, see the <ulink url=\"http://www.fs-"
"security.com/docs.php\">Firestarter Online Manual</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:107(title)
msgid "Avoid Internet nuisances and crime"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:108(para)
msgid ""
"From time to time, you may be sent an email which carries a virus or links "
"to a fraudulent website. This type of email is very common, and it is "
"important to learn how to deal with it, in order to prevent your computer or "
"your personal details from being compromised or misused."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:109(para)
msgid ""
"Such messages are often received from total strangers. However, sometimes an "
"email may appear to be from someone you know, when really it is not. This is "
"because it is possible to include a fake sender email address in emails."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:110(para)
msgid ""
"Unwanted (unsolicited) mail tends to fall in to one of several categories:"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:112(para)
msgid "Spam (junk) email, where people offer unwanted services and products"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:113(para)
msgid ""
"Scam emails, where people pretend to ask for help in exchange for large sums "
"of money"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:114(para)
msgid ""
"Phishing email, where the message appears to be from a bank or other online "
"service, asking you to enter your personal and financial details, or "
"passwords."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:117(para)
msgid "Below are some tips for keeping safe online:"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:120(para)
msgid ""
"You should never reply to unsolicited mail, or even click on the links in "
"the mail. Doing so usually results in more junk mail being sent to you."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:121(para)
msgid ""
"Never click on links in emails which lead to websites asking for your "
"password or similar. It is possible for the text of the link to give one "
"address, when really it opens up another (possibly dangerous) address. "
"Instead, type the link into your web browser yourself and proceed from there."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:122(para)
msgid ""
"If a website asks for your financial details, ensure that it is secure. In "
"the <application>Firefox Web browser</application>, secure websites have a "
"<emphasis>yellow</emphasis> address bar with a padlock icon to the right of "
"the address. Click on the padlock to read more information about the "
"security of the website."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:123(para)
msgid ""
"Only download and run software from sources that you trust. By default, you "
"can only download software directly from Ubuntu."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:127(title)
msgid "Make backup copies of your files"
msgstr "Faites des copies de sauvegarde de vos fichiers"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:128(para)
msgid ""
"A problem which you may occasionally encounter is the unexpected loss of "
"some of your work and settings for one reason or another. The causes of such "
"<emphasis>data loss</emphasis> are many and varied; it could be anything "
"from a power cut to accidentally deleting a file. It is highly recommended "
"that you make regular back-up copies of your important files so that, if you "
"do encounter a problem, you will not have lost those files."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:130(para)
msgid ""
"It is wise to store back-up copies of files separately from your computer; "
"that is, you should make use of some form of file storage which is not "
"permanently attached to your computer. Options include:"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:132(para)
msgid "Writable CDs and DVDs"
msgstr "CDs et DVDs enregistrables"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:133(para)
msgid "External hard disks and flash memory devices"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:134(para)
msgid "Another computer on the network"
msgstr "Un autre ordinateur sur le réseau"

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:137(para)
msgid ""
"A simple way of backing-up your files is to manually copy them to a safe "
"location (see above) by using the <application>File Browser</application>."
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:138(para)
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can use a dedicated back-up application, such as "
"<application>HUBackup</application>:"
msgstr ""

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:142(para)
msgid ""
"Install the <application>hubackup</application> package from the "
"<quote>Universe</quote> repository (see <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"ghelp:add-"
"applications\">Add Applications</ulink>)."
msgstr ""
"Installez le paquet <application>hubackup</application> à partir du dépôt "
"<quote>Universe</quote> (voir <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"ghelp:add-"
"applications\">Ajouter des applications</ulink>)."

#: keeping-safe/C/keeping-safe.xml:145(para)
msgid ""
